"{\"uid\": \"lbc.co.uk-article-olympic-star-adam-peaty-breaks-silence-after-testing-positive-for-covid-5Hjcnqt_2\", \"text\": \"By Henry Moore  Adam Peaty won silver in the 100m breaststroke final - after Italian Nicol\\u00c3\\u00b2 Martinenghi denied Team GB their first gold in Paris by two-hundredths of a second.  Adam Peaty paid tribute to partner Holly Ramsay after testing positive for Covid just hours after winning silver in the 100m breaststroke at Paris 2024.  Peaty swam 59.05 - but was pipped by Nicol\\u00c3\\u00b2 Martinenghi who swam 59.03 to win gold in the pool.  The Olympic record-holder had suggested he felt unwell after securing second place and his symptoms only worsened after the final.  \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cAdam Peaty began feeling unwell on Sunday, ahead of his Men\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s 100m Breaststroke final,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d Team GB said in a statement.  \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cIn the hours after the final, his symptoms became worse and he was tested for COVID early on Monday morning. He tested positive at that point.  Read more:Olympics LIVE: Team GB wins two golds on Day 3 of Paris Olympics  Read more:Becky Downie emotional as she makes return to Olympics after 8 years after overcoming family tragedy  \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cHe is hopeful to be back in competition for the relay events later in the swimming programme.  \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cAs in any case of illness, the situation is being managed appropriately, with all usual precautions being taken to keep the wider delegation healthy.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  Taking to Instagram in the wake of the news, Peaty said: \\\"A night full of raw emotion and sport in its true form.  \\\"These last 14 months have been incredibly testing and I do not regret one training session or decision I made.  \\\"I\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099ve continued to fight and find new ways to enjoy something that has broken me to the core and to end up with an Olympic silver through all of that is an absolute blessing.  \\\"I\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099m more proud of the man and athlete I am from last night than I have been across my entire career.\\\"  This diagnosis casts doubt over Peaty\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s hopes of winning more medals at the Paris 2024 games.  If able to recover in time, the swimmer would play a key role in Great Britain\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s men\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s and mixed 4x100m medley relay quartets.  The men\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s final is due to take place on August 4, while the mixed race is scheduled for the day before.  Speaking after his silver medal win, Peaty admitted to feeling unwell: \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cI\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099ve had a bit of a curveball with my throat but, please, it\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s no excuse at all.  \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cBut it\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s a curveball I\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099ve had to respond to.  \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cYou can train eight years for something and not feel 100 per cent on the day and (not being) 100 per cent costs you 0.02 seconds, that\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s just the way it is.  \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cI\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099m so happy to pass the baton to Nicolo because I\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099ve been racing him for so long. All I could see in my eyes were Qin and Arno.  \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cThey are two of the best executors in that final, but that\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s just sport. I got a little bit blindsided, I touched the wall and I truly believed I got it but it wasn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t meant to be.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  The use of the Ajax vehicle was halted for two weeks to allow an investigation to be carried out  1h ago  The Home Secretary and Foreign Secretary said they had reached \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009can arrangement\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d with the Chinese government on \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cconsolidating\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d Beijing\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s diplomatic presence in one site  1h ago  The former 'I am A Celebrity' contestant told followers she was suffering from inflammation all over her body  2h ago  The star told fans he had been dealing with a \\\"lot of health issues over the last year\\\"  3h ago  The Supreme Court ruling said the words \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cwoman\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d and \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009csex\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d in the Equality Act 2010 refer to a biological woman and biological sex  4h ago  Disney fans confused as to why animation needed different titles across the Atlantic  4h ago  With his side losing 17-7 to the New England Patriots on Monday, Koo lined up a 47-yard field goal attempt, as he had done many times before  4h ago  The use of the Ajax vehicle was halted for two weeks to allow an investigation to be carried out  1h ago  The Home Secretary and Foreign Secretary said they had reached \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009can arrangement\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d with the Chinese government on \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cconsolidating\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d Beijing\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s diplomatic presence in one site  1h ago  The Supreme Court ruling said the words \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cwoman\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d and \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009csex\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d in the Equality Act 2010 refer to a biological woman and biological sex  4h ago  The officers made \\\"concerted efforts\\\"  to blame fans in the aftermath  5h ago  A 'quality issue' with metal fuselage panels on multiple\\u00c2\\u00a0A320 models has been discovered.  6h ago  A dozen prisoners have been mistakenly freed in the past month with two remaining at large.  8h ago  Other big name actors such as Dame Judi Dench and Brian Cox are also supporting Age UK's campaign against loneliness.  9h ago  Follow us:  About & Help  Get The LBC App  Legal & Info  Business & Careers  \\u00c2\\u00a9 Global 2025 | 30 Leicester Square, London, WC2H 7LA  Copyright Global 2025. 30 Leicester Square, London. W C 2 H 7 L A.\"}"